main function of javascript = new Date();

dates begins with milliseconds
first date counted: 01/01/1970

declaring with milliseconds
var dt = new Date(0);
dt = Wed Dec 31 1969 21:00:00 GMT-0300 (BRT)

declaring with a date
var dt = new Date(Date.parse("March 10, 2001"));
dr = Sat Mar 10 2001 00:00:00 GMT-0300 (BRT)

keep actual date
var dt = new Date();

show actual year
dt.getFullYear();

show actual month (0~11, 0 = january, 11 = december)
dt.getMonth();

brazilian months name
var months = ["Janeiro", "Fevereiro", "Março", "Abril", "Maio", "Junho", "Julho", "Agosto", "Setembro", "Outubro", "Novembro", "Dezembro"]
months[dt.getMonth()];

show actual week's day (0~6, 0 = sunday, 6 = saturday)
dt.getDay();

brazilian week days names
var days = ["Domingo","Segunda", "Terça", "Quarta", "Quinta", "Sexta", "Sabado"];
days[dt.getDay()];

show actual month's day (1~31)
dt.getDate();

show actual hours
dt.getHours();

show actual minutes
dt.getMinutes();

show actual seconds
dt.getSeconds();

show total miliseconds from 0 to actual date
dt.getMilliseconds();

brazilian date format
dt.getDate()+"/"+(dt.getMonth()+1)+"/"+dt.getFullYear();

adding X days to a date
dt.setDate(dt.getDate() + X);

adding X hours to a date
dt.setHours(dt.getHours() + X);